[para]
[:en] A [+uniform random bit generator[%]] [`g] of type [`G] is a function
object returning unsigned integer values such that each value in the range of
possible results has (ideally) equal probability of being returned.
[:zh_CN] [`G] 类型的[+均匀随机位生成器[%]] [`g] 是返回无符号整数值的函数对象，其
可能结果的范围中的每个值都具有（理想）相等的返回概率。

[enter:note]
[:en] The degree to which [`g][=']s results approximate the ideal is often
determined statistically.
[:zh_CN] [`g] 的结果在何种程度上近似于理想，通常是由统计确定的。
[exit:note]

[para]
[:en] A class [`G] satisfies the requirements of a [+uniform random bit
generator[%]] if the expressions shown in [#UniformRandomBitGenerator] are valid
and have the indicated semantics, and if [`G] also satisfies all other
requirements of this subclause [#rand.req.urng].
[:zh_CN] 如果 [#UniformRandomBitGenerator] 中给出的表达式均有效并具有所指定的
语义，并且如果 [`G] 还满足本子条款 [#rand.req.urng] 中的其他全部规定，则类 [`G]
满足[+均匀随机位生成器[%]]的规定。


[:en] In that Table and throughout this subclause:
[:zh_CN] 在这个表和本子条款的通篇中：

[list:ol@arparen]
[item]
[:en] [`T] is the type named by [`G][=']s associated [`result_type], and
[:zh_CN] [`T] 是 [`G] 所关联的 [`result_type] 所指名的类型，而
[item]
[:en] [`g] is a value of [`G].
[:zh_CN] [`g] 为 [`G] 的值。
[list:end]

